# Byproducts of the differential test (see README.md).  None of these are sources: the
# Int256_ oracle is *fetched* from kvx-lao by extract-int256.sh so that it stays whatever
# kvx-lao says it is, and everything else is generated from the core's own tables --
# regs.inc/shims.inc from Behavior.tuple (genregs.py), bounds.inc from Opcode.table
# (genbounds.py), opstubs.inc from the tuple's own prototypes (genstubs.py).  All three are
# core-specific, which is exactly why none of them is checked in.
/int256/
/harness
/opstubs.inc
/regs.inc
/shims.inc
/bounds.inc
/*.txt
